<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Thousands of Barclays and Barclaycard customers have been left unable to access their money as the mobile apps have crashed.</p>

<p>The bank confirmed that it is having issues with its services, with some being unavailable, on its service update page. </p>

<p>Barclays website says: 'We're sorry if you're having trouble logging in to our app – we're working to fix this.'</p>

<p>Thousands of Barclays and Barclaycard customers have been left unable to access their money as the mobile apps have crashed</p>

<p>Complaints have been flooding in from thousands of disgruntled customers unable to access their money, The Sun reported. </p>

<p>Outage tracker Downdetector saw complaints beginning to come in at around midday, with more than 1,000 complaints being recorded.</p>

<p>Barclays said on its website that customers should be able to access their accounts on its website, or equally through telephone banking.</p>

<p>Customers have been complaining to the bank on Twitter this afternoon.</p>

<p>One person said: 'When you are on your break and need to transfer money over to get food but the Barclays app is down.' </p>
